attributes.description: Generate metrics from OTel profiling data.

embeddableConfig.description: This panel shows CPU consumption split into two exclusive categories: user (code executing in userspace) and kernel (code executing in kernelspace).
embeddableConfig.title: User / Kernel CPU (exclusive)

embeddableConfig.description:
This panel shows CPU consumption for code executing in userspace (exclusively) split into categories, according to the frame type.

Different higher-level runtimes (e.g.Python, JVM) have different frame types. The Native frame type corresponds to natively compiled code (e.g. Rust, C, C++) excluding Golang which has its own frame type.
embeddableConfig.title: User CPU by frame type (exclusive)

embeddableConfig.description: This panel shows CPU consumption for native (e.g Rust, C, C++) code executing in userspace (exclusively) split into categories according to shared library.
embeddableConfig.title: User CPU by shared library (exclusive)

embeddableConfig.description: This panel shows CPU consumption for code executing in kernelspace split into categories according to identified system call.
embeddableConfig.title: Kernel CPU by system call

embeddableConfig.description: This panel shows CPU consumption for code executing in kernelspace split into different categories.
embeddableConfig.title: Kernel CPU by category over time

embeddableConfig.description: This panel shows CPU consumption for code executing in kernelspace performing network I/O.
embeddableConfig.title: Kernel CPU by network I/O

embeddableConfig.description: This panel shows CPU consumption for code executing in kernelspace split into different categories.
embeddableConfig.title: Kernel CPU by category

embeddableConfig.description: This panels shows CPU consumption for code executing in kernelspace performing IPC I/O.
embeddableConfig.title: Kernel CPU by IPC I/O

embeddableConfig.description: This panel shows CPU consumption for code executing in kernelspace performing disk I/O.
embeddableConfig.title: Kernel CPU by disk I/O
